article.headline: The Citadel 67, Chowan 53
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Cameron Wells scored 22 points and The Citadel defeated Chowan 67-53 Friday. Wells, who on Dec. 23 supplanted Regan Truesdale as The Citadel's all-time leading scorer, also had six rebounds and three steals. The Bulldogs beat the Hawks for the third time in as many meetings since they first played in 2003. Quinton McDuffie had 16 points and 11 rebounds to lead Chowan (1-7), but he was the Hawks' only player in double figures. Bryan Streeter scored 11 points and Zach Urbanus added 10 for the Bulldogs (5-8). Mike Groselle's 10 rebounds helped The Citadel win the battle of the boards 49-32, which compensated for the Bulldogs' poor shooting. They made only 22 of 56 from the field (39.3 percent), but that still proved better than Chowan's 34.5 percent (20 of 58). Groselle also had eight points.

statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.
